      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**MEMORANDUM**\n\n**TO:** All Relevant Parties\n\n**FROM:** [Your Name]\n\n**SUBJECT:** Enhanced Know Your Customer (KYC) Compliance Procedures\n\n**PURPOSE:**\n\nIn accordance with applicable regulatory requirements and industry standards, this memorandum outlines the enhanced Know Your Customer (KYC) compliance procedures for our onboarding process. These procedures are designed to ensure the collection and verification of required customer information, adherence to anti-money laundering (AML) and combating the financing of terrorism (CFT) regulations, and compliance with relevant data protection and confidentiality standards.\n\n**I. INTRODUCTION**\n\n1.1. In order to comply with the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) of 1970, as amended, and the USA PATRIOT Act of 2001, we are required to implement robust KYC procedures to verify the identity of our customers.\n\n**II. CUSTOMER IDENTIFICATION**\n\n2.1. Upon initial customer contact, we will request the following information:\n\n* Full name\n* Date of birth\n* Government-issued identification number (e.g., passport, driver's license, state ID)\n* Residential address\n* Business address (if applicable)\n* Occupation\n* Source of funds (if applicable",
